        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 2:37PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 236 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 25
miles southwest of Geyser, or 31 miles north of White Sulphur
Springs, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Neihart.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
